This place is not the same I have had bad experiences after ordering for a while.  1) I ordered a portion of red beans and the only thing I got was more water and not beans at all.  2) I decided to give it another chance and after I ordered I discovered they charge me twice and it took more than 2 weeks to get my money back.  3) Last chance I ordered a combo #1 and I found a rock inside the chicken and I almost broke my tooth. I've ordered from this resturant a few times. They're food is tasty and the portions are generous. However, my most recent experience was unpleasant. I ordered delivery and there was a $20 pepper steak dish missing from my bag, so I called the resturant. Their offer was for me to walk/drive over to the resturant and pick up the missing dish myself, because in their point of view, "the delivery person probably lost it", so what can they do. I told them I don't have the time that day, but can come by the next day.  The next day, I called ahead 45 minutes beforehand, and when I arrived there, the peppersteak wasn't ready. They actually did not even start cooking my dish. The manager or whomever gave me the excuse it was because he did not want the food to spoil (delivery can take up to an hour, so I really don't believe that excuse at all). As I did not have another 20 minutes to waste standing there, I left and took the loss. Everyone was well-mannered, but the experience as a whole was rather dissapointing.

Came here with a friend and we both left pretty satisfied with the food we were served. Ordered the breaded steak with rice and beans and never did I see coming so much food! I was expecting everything on one plate and yet I received two plates; one for the steak and some side salad, and the rice and beans on another plate. The food's taste and amount sure do deserve the price they have. My friend even gave me a piece of the grilled steak he ordered and it left me wanting for more. The only reason I am giving it 4 stars is because the side salad was dry and there was no dressing with it. Furthermore, the lettuce was served in large amounts and there was a part that tasted like dirt so I had to skip on the lettuce altogether.  Other than that, I recommend this place!

I'll keep visiting to see how it develops and will adjust my review accordingly. It's nice to have a Cuban spot in the neighborhood.

So i placed my first order with these guys the other nite. First off it took nearly an hour to get my food. As for the food it was a mixed bag. While the Cuban Sandwich was delicious, the chicharron de pollo was on the terrible side. It's SUPPOSE to be CRISPY and they were more like boneless chicken nuggets with an underwhelming flavor. The UPSIDE the portions are generous BUT had to throw out the leftovers of those "chicken nuggets" LoL as i had NO desire to eat anymore...Yikes...well too bad. wanted to like this place but might just get their Cubanos whenever i get the craving for a few of those sandwiches...cheers.

Also, if you’re here during the day, be sure to say hello to Fidel in the attached flower shop.

Beautifully decorated, spacious and welcomed addition to the neighborhood. Papa rellena and chorizo appetizer were both delicious and quite sizeable! We shared the chofan mixto which was perfectly seasoned and big enough for two of us. Quick and courteous service. My only gripe is that this is really a dominican restaurant costumed as a Cuban restaurant. A couple of Cuban dishes sprinkle this very very Dominican menu. Basically Malecón with the addition of ropa  vieja. They didn’t have Media noche bread which to a Cuban like me is sacrilegious. I will def give it another chance and hopefully the mojitos will be more natural tasting. Some sort of flavored syrup gave it a cough syrup aftertaste. Great music!

The lunch specials are only $10 and the portions  are substantial.  Definitely a place to visit often.  If you find review helpful, click like.
